Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.41,0:00:02.98,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Flowing water has no form.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.98,0:00:04.71,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A blowing wind can't be seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.71,0:00:06.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}All cases can be freely deduced!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.68,0:00:08.75,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today is a special with cursed masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.75,0:00:10.95,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A mysterious room and an eerie smile!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.95,0:00:12.59,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.59,0:00:14.01,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.01,0:00:16.86,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.60,0:01:45.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad, drive careful, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.01,0:01:46.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.14,0:01:49.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, you're going to be performing on a charity show held for children
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.14,0:01:52.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who have lost their families in car accidents next week, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.08,0:01:54.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you get into an accident in a place like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.02,0:01:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we couldn't face up to Beniko Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the hostess who chose you as a guest!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.13,0:02:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.96,0:02:05.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} invited us to a party today too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.63,0:02:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I get in an accident, I'll miss out on all the good food!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.63,0:02:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.11,0:02:14.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} used to be a famous singer, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.81,0:02:16.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.13,0:02:19.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She used to a big star. They called her the Canary of the Orient.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.84,0:02:22.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But nowadays she's so busy being the president
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.03,0:02:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of a show-biz promotion company called Kurenai Promotion
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.88,0:02:27.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that she's hardly ever on stage anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.84,0:02:37.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.89,0:02:39.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.36,0:02:41.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is this tree lying in the middle of the road like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.43,0:02:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, there's something posted on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.33,0:02:47.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.70,0:02:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't take part in the charity party held by Beniko Suo. You'll regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.11,0:02:57.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Messenger of the Cursed Masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.38,0:02:58.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.41,0:02:59.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that supposed to mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.91,0:03:02.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Messenger of the Cursed Masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.04,0:03:24.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.40,0:03:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is some mansion, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.01,0:03:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.41,0:03:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masanori Katagiri, the photographer...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.42,0:03:40.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the one who travels around the world taking pictures of beautiful landscapes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.75,0:03:41.30,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Masanori Katagiri (45)\NPhotographer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.22,0:03:52.85,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mamoru Matsudaira (24)\NPro Baseball Player
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.56,0:03:50.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The King of Home Runs, baseball player Mamoru Matsudaira?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.30,0:03:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? And you're that famous detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.43,0:03:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.30,0:03:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.99,0:03:59.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you guests on next week's charity show too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.37,0:04:00.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.81,0:04:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a beauty!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.95,0:04:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's Haruka Nagara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.65,0:04:13.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the tarot card reader who's all the rage on TV and in the magazines?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.89,0:04:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know her too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.89,0:04:18.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whenever I step up to the plate, I read her predictions
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.83,0:04:22.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and put on gloves that match her lucky color of the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.23,0:04:24.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And that's how you became the King of Home Runs?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.57,0:04:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.70,0:04:29.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What seems to be the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.01,0:04:35.06,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Haruka Nagara (25)\NTarot Card Reader
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.90,0:04:34.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel something ominous about this mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.11,0:04:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I feel that there is going to be a great disaster...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.38,0:04:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What an eerie thing to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.91,0:04:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, rather than talk out here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.85,0:04:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,shouldn't we ask to be let in?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.65,0:04:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.45,0:04:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But which door do we use to get into the mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.13,0:04:54.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are two entrances...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.80,0:05:01.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you all for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.13,0:05:03.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, so that side's the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.14,0:05:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you all for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.61,0:05:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:16.77,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Honami Shimogasa (21)\NSuo House Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.15,0:05:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} and his party, please enter from this side—the east entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.15,0:05:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.31,0:05:25.40,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Minaho Shimogasa (21)\NSuo House Maid
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.69,0:05:22.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}, Matsudaira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} and Nagara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.75,0:05:25.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,please enter from this side—the west entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.26,0:05:28.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are we going in separately?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.50,0:05:32.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The inside of this mansion is divided into west and east.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.20,0:05:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those who will be spending the night in the rooms on the west side,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.83,0:05:36.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,enter from the west entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.07,0:05:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those who will be spending the night in the rooms on the east side,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.91,0:05:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,enter from the east entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.78,0:05:44.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is a tradition practiced here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.21,0:05:47.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What a strange place.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.98,0:05:50.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we don't stick to traditional practices in this mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.95,0:05:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grave misfortune will befall us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.02,0:05:55.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misfortune?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.69,0:05:56.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What makes you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:05:58.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because this is the place where...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.63,0:06:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because this is the place where...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.69,0:06:04.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- ...the cursed masks reside.\N- ...the cursed masks reside.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.50,0:06:10.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cursed masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.56,0:06:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's one here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.23,0:06:36.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} likes to collect masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.63,0:06:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.18,0:06:52.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This one's a cat mask...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.68,0:06:57.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your luggage has already been brought here,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.28,0:07:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so please wait in the mask room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.62,0:07:02.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mask room?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.06,0:07:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.47,0:07:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.20,0:07:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.84,0:07:19.18,Signs,,0,0,0,,E
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.84,0:07:19.18,Signs,,0,0,0,,2ND FLOOR
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.84,0:07:19.18,Signs,,0,0,0,,W
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.84,0:07:19.18,Signs,,0,0,0,,MASK ROOM
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.60,0:07:19.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This room connects the east and west wings of the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.64,0:07:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, this is fantastic!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.47,0:07:22.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are so many masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.32,0:07:40.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at all this...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.20,0:07:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.40,0:07:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A remote control?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.48,0:07:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What the...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.23,0:07:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.01,0:07:59.11,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}W-What's with all these masks?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.68,0:08:01.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is all this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.95,0:08:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are all these masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.75,0:08:05.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are called the masks of Jofre{drop back and punt... there's no way you can get this from Joburuu, but at least this name exists in Spain, and it's what Catalan uses, so mnyeh}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.72,0:08:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You are...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.98,0:08:12.65,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Beniko Suo (63)\NSinger ∙ President of Kurenai Promotion
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.29,0:08:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beniko Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.96,0:08:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much, everyone, for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.24,0:08:18.74,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kazuyo Inaba (40)\NSuo's Secretary
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.47,0:08:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you like my precious collection?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.14,0:08:26.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, yes, well, I guess you could say...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.41,0:08:28.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just mentioned the masks of Jofre,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.78,0:08:31.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but are you referring to the masks covering the side wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.68,0:08:34.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it is said that the Spanish sculptor,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.28,0:08:37.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jofre Gonzales, made them just before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.52,0:08:39.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are the two hundred masks that he made.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.95,0:08:42.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are also called the Cursed Masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.29,0:08:45.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cursed Masks?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.09,0:08:49.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, what are these cursed masks all about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.50,0:08:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jofre Gonzales is a sculptor of tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.03,0:08:54.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although overflowing with talent,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.93,0:08:57.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,trapped by the jealousy of his brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.60,0:09:01.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,his fame, glory and estate were all taken away from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.64,0:09:04.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Jofre, who became very wary of people,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.41,0:09:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,began making masks as if obsessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.25,0:09:13.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After finishing his two-hundredth mask, he killed himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.12,0:09:16.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks were scattered upon his body and splattered with blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.49,0:09:20.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as if they had sucked the blood from him while he was still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.99,0:09:23.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since then, Jofre's reputation was restored,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.93,0:09:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and his masks were handed down to various people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.27,0:09:31.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But many who owned the masks seem to have died tragically.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.14,0:09:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An English bank president fell off his horse
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.68,0:09:39.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the following day after getting hold of one of the masks, and died.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.21,0:09:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A French jeweler was attacked by robbers and killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.62,0:09:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And with the passing of time, these masks became known
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.19,0:09:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as the cursed masks that sip the blood of their owners,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.06,0:09:52.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and were feared by people.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.76,0:09:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, owning all two hundred of those masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.90,0:09:58.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No need to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.33,0:10:03.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had a master spiritualist seal the curse in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.10,0:10:06.94,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's starting to get more and more occult around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.51,0:10:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.51,0:10:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the evil will of a living person may be even more frightening than a curse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.31,0:10:16.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.45,0:10:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, on our way here, our path was blocked by a fallen tree,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.38,0:10:22.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and we found this pinned to the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.52,0:10:27.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! I received a similar letter three days ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.66,0:10:30.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got one too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.13,0:10:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.27,0:10:33.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.00,0:10:36.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It seems to be more than just a prank...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.24,0:10:39.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that the office also sent me a strange letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.87,0:10:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toya, you're late!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.05,0:10:46.85,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Toya Aikawa (26)\NRock Singer
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.48,0:10:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm right in the midst of a nationwide tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.91,0:10:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.21,0:10:49.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.48,0:10:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, don't you know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.15,0:10:55.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the popular #1 rock singer Toya Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.36,0:10:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You received a strange letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.16,0:10:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The name of the sender is not written.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.16,0:11:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The way the name of the addressee is written is also odd.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.70,0:11:07.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems a ruler was used so that the handwriting cannot be identified.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.17,0:11:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I open it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.94,0:11:12.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.24,0:11:17.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.61,0:11:22.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cursed masks will sip blood tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.11,0:11:24.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Messenger of the Cursed Masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:28.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you should call the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.89,0:11:30.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.62,0:11:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since I've started the charity show, I've been bothered by pranks like these.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.57,0:11:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, this stew is very delicious indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.45,0:11:49.08,Character Card,,0,0,0,,East Wing, First Floor\NDining Room
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.04,0:11:47.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This wine sure is good too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.04,0:11:49.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Top class!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.84,0:11:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, I am greatly thankful
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.78,0:11:55.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that you have all graciously accepted to appear as guests
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.72,0:11:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on the charity show that I will be hosting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.85,0:12:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, may I ask you a question?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.19,0:12:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.72,0:12:07.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you come across the idea of saving children
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.06,0:12:09.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,whose parents who have become victims of traffic accidents?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.33,0:12:13.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I started this charity about 15 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.97,0:12:21.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to tell the truth, my manager caused a hit-and-run accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.47,0:12:22.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A hit-and-run?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.61,0:12:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Ever since then,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.51,0:12:28.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could not stand being indifferent to traffic accidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.35,0:12:33.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are people saying that she's a publicity seeker,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.49,0:12:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but it's really nothing like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.46,0:12:39.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um... What happened to the manager after the incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.53,0:12:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.93,0:12:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That manager happened to be my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.33,0:12:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.00,0:12:48.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I lost my father at a young age,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.94,0:12:51.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after my mother died, I was sent around to my relatives' homes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.80,0:12:53.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really had it tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.27,0:12:57.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} here helped me in every way she could.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.41,0:13:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm what I am today thanks to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.35,0:13:06.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toya's mother was more a cherished friend of mine than a manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.99,0:13:08.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are many at Kurenai Promotion
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.89,0:13:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who have lost their families in traffic accidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.26,0:13:14.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0} is putting a lot of effort in helping the children
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.66,0:13:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of traffic accident victims become independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.33,0:13:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a touching story!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.53,0:13:24.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll cooperate as much as I can at your charity show next week!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.80,0:13:25.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.41,0:13:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, I lost my wife in a car accident 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.64,0:13:32.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure that my wife in heaven is happy
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.55,0:13:34.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,that I'm going to be taking part in Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s charity show too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.31,0:13:42.69,Character Card,,0,0,0,,West Wing, Third Floor\NSuo's Living Room
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.85,0:13:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I'd like you to investigate something for me, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.19,0:13:44.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.66,0:13:47.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'd like me to figure out the one who sent out those letters, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.86,0:13:48.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.20,0:13:53.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I wonder if you can check in detail
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.17,0:13:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,on the traffic accident that took Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.14,0:13:58.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.07,0:14:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,May I ask you why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.87,0:14:02.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is something that bothers me...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.34,0:14:05.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would 2 million yen be enough to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.21,0:14:07.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,2 million yen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.75,0:14:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd be more than glad to!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.79,0:14:18.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're pretty good, King of Home Runs!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.79,0:14:19.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.04,0:14:23.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, you play very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.26,0:14:28.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, this year is a good year for you to begin something new.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.87,0:14:30.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something new?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.87,0:14:34.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why then, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, how about making a debut as a singer from our company?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.06,0:14:40.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it'll make a great hit if it is sung by\Nthe modern-day great detective, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.18,0:14:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess I'll sing you a song then!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.68,0:14:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- We're sorry...\N- We're sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.55,0:14:48.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone, when the clock strikes midnight,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.62,0:14:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we have a tradition of locking the door of the mask room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.86,0:14:53.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the door is locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.46,0:14:56.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we will not be able to pass back and forth between the east and west wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.82,0:15:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we would like you to go into your rooms before that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.54,0:15:03.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.94,0:15:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Midnight is still too early to close up...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.14,0:15:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a reason for locking the doors at midnight?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.00,0:15:12.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks of Jofre like pranks
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.95,0:15:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and begin playing on their own come midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.45,0:15:18.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we must lock the door and keep them confined.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.84,0:15:20.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.45,0:15:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.76,0:15:25.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come morning, the masks are tilted unnaturally...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.76,0:15:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...or down on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.63,0:15:29.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This has happened many times now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.20,0:15:34.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,- Now, please go into your rooms, everyone.\N- Now, please go into your rooms, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.10,0:15:38.91,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Can this story get any more occult?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.28,0:16:37.24,Character Card,,0,0,0,,East Wing, Second Floor\NGuest Room
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.06,0:16:41.06,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ugh, his snoring is so loud{lit. annoying}, I can't sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.64,0:16:45.74,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}An extension phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.91,0:16:50.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.24,0:16:53.69,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The Messenger of the Cursed Masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.69,0:16:55.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Messenger of the Cursed Masks?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.25,0:16:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gimme that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.32,0:16:58.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.99,0:17:02.05,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The cursed masks thirst for blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.05,0:17:04.72,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Who will be the sacrifice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.72,0:17:05.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.92,0:17:07.69,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}You'd better hurry before it's too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.39,0:17:10.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.13,0:17:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.40,0:17:19.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, Conan, wake Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} up and bring the key to this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.97,0:17:20.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.83,0:17:43.06,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's locked...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.96,0:17:46.03,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The call a while ago was from an extension.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.03,0:17:48.25,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The person is in the mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.97,0:17:51.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.44,0:17:53.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the key!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.91,0:17:54.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.56,0:18:04.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.78,0:18:07.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks of Jofre are gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.12,0:18:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.06,0:18:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that just now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.99,0:18:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It came from above!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.60,0:18:19.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Above? That's Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bedroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.13,0:18:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't go that way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.07,0:18:28.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to get to her room, you have to take the stairs on the west side!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.98,0:18:35.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This door is locked too...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.11,0:18:36.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll wake Minaho and make her open the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.25,0:18:39.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what on earth is this racket about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.12,0:18:40.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the middle of the night...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.35,0:18:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks of Jofre are...?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.86,0:18:52.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck is going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.21,0:19:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.34,0:19:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This door is locked too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.08,0:19:07.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Break that glass!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.88,0:19:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, what are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.08,0:19:15.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did something happen to Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.17,0:19:29.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, how's {\i1}Sensei{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.37,0:19:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like she's hurt. She's bleeding badly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.64,0:19:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks of Jofre are scattered all over the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.57,0:19:36.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The masks of Jofre?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.84,0:19:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any other way in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.58,0:19:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's another door over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.94,0:19:44.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That door's no good!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.95,0:19:46.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been sealed off for quite a while already!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.02,0:19:50.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go in through there and check out the inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.16,0:19:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess there is no other choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.69,0:19:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad! Here you go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.57,0:20:01.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.21,0:20:09.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The door is looked, all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.48,0:20:11.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Two locks!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.88,0:20:13.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry and go check on Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.49,0:20:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.36,0:20:26.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No good... We're too late...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.49,0:20:27.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Son of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.99,0:20:30.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.44,0:20:44.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.22,0:20:47.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't come in! Please stay here!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.58,0:20:52.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her throat slashed with one stroke...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.85,0:20:54.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How cruel...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.45,0:20:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.12,0:20:57.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was this a murder?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.32,0:20:58.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.66,0:21:00.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door was locked, wasn't it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.73,0:21:04.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the looks of the corpse, suicide is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.49,0:21:04.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.26,0:21:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My curse has been fulfilled...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.47,0:21:10.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.00,0:21:13.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a declaration that a murder will be committed,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.97,0:21:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,from the Messenger of the Cursed Masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.61,0:21:22.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.75,0:21:24.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curse of the masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.55,0:21:27.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was cursed to death by the masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.69,0:21:30.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Suo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was cursed to death by the masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.89,0:21:32.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.56,0:21:34.86,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But the crime scene is a locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.36,0:21:38.93,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How did the murderer manage to kill Suo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.00,0:21:48.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Messenger of the Cursed Masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.00,0:21:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you report it to the police when you first found this letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.81,0:21:57.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, the victim, Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} mentioned that she had been receiving
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.38,0:22:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,similar pranks for some time, and not to worry about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.35,0:22:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, these are the cursed masks...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.15,0:22:04.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.02,0:22:09.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We heard a groan and a loud crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.89,0:22:13.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could've been the sound of the killer scattering the masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.56,0:22:17.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said that this door was locked from inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.50,0:22:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's why I broke the glass above the door, made Conan go inside
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.43,0:22:24.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and verified Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.97,0:22:27.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door was definitely locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.64,0:22:28.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both locks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.04,0:22:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two locks?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.01,0:22:30.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.04,0:22:34.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} always locked both locks on her door.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.25,0:22:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.62,0:22:37.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,this lock...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.38,0:22:40.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and then this padlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.37,0:22:43.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why did the victim have two locks on her door?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.22,0:22:46.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, according to her secretary, Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.36,0:22:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} went to have the curse of the masks sealed in by a spiritualist,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.10,0:22:54.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,she was told to do several things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.63,0:23:00.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them was to put two locks on the bedroom door.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.24,0:23:02.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A spiritualist, eh...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.37,0:23:08.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the victim herself opened the door and let the victim in?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.25,0:23:11.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it doesn't seem like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.79,0:23:15.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was suffering from insomnia lately,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.79,0:23:17.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and was taking sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.59,0:23:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why there were no traces of the victim struggling?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.43,0:23:27.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the victim locked the door as usual, took sleeping pills and went to bed,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.80,0:23:30.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,how did the killer get into the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.34,0:23:32.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this door?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.90,0:23:35.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a bedroom next door too,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.47,0:23:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but that door seems to have been closed off for many years.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.55,0:23:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems to be nailed shut,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.45,0:23:42.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and there are no signs of it having been opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.22,0:23:47.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The railing above the door, can that bar be removed?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.95,0:23:51.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I checked on it, but it couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.29,0:23:53.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The space between the bars is about 5 or 6 centimeters,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.26,0:23:54.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so not even an arm can go through.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.83,0:23:57.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about that window on the other side?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.56,0:23:59.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That window is fixed on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.70,0:24:01.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is nothing out of the ordinary about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.10,0:24:06.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so, how and where did the killer go in and out of this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.17,0:24:11.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only door that could be opened and shut was locked from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.64,0:24:14.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door to the bedroom next door is nailed and sealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.85,0:24:16.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The space between the bars above it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.22,0:24:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is so narrow that not even an arm can get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.62,0:24:20.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The windows are both fixed on,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.42,0:24:22.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and there seems to be nothing wrong with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.72,0:24:25.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's also impossible for the victim herself to have opened the door
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.42,0:24:28.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and let the killer in, because she was under the effect of sleeping pills.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.56,0:24:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The room is a locked room, with no way in or out.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.30,0:24:35.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really took the sleeping pills herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.00,0:24:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she didn't take them herself, who would make her...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.64,0:24:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Wait a sec...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.64,0:24:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.71,0:24:45.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.91,0:24:48.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer met Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in the middle of the night,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.28,0:24:50.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,made her drink something with a sleeping pill in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.62,0:24:51.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and put her to sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.85,0:24:55.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the killer carried Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to her bed and killed her there!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.52,0:24:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.66,0:25:00.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, how did the killer lock the door when leaving the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.39,0:25:02.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.66,0:25:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I haven't figured that out yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.96,0:25:06.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.13,0:25:10.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Only half of the locked room mystery can be explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.07,0:25:15.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door is the only possible way that the killer could've entered,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.67,0:25:19.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but how did the killer lock the door from the outside?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.68,0:25:21.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the lock were just a handle that could be turned,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.68,0:25:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then using a string or something could unlock it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.57,0:25:25.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the problem is the padlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.78,0:25:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to lock this, the door has to be closed first.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.82,0:25:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the door and the metal piece on the door frame have to be matched.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.22,0:25:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only after doing that can the pole be stuck into the two metal fixtures.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.30,0:25:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's possible to do all this from outside the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.57,0:25:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of trick did the killer use?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.44,0:25:47.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No matter what trick the killer used,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.47,0:25:49.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}why didn't the killer make it look like a suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.57,0:25:53.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}after doing all this to kill her?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.18,0:25:57.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The killer called our room just before the murder was committed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.12,0:26:00.89,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As if to let us know beforehand that murder was going to take place...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.79,0:26:04.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This knife seems to be the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.12,0:26:07.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is what was decorated in the room of the masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.16,0:26:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was poked into the bed pole, but there's something odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.60,0:26:15.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you can see, its handle is also smeared with blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.03,0:26:18.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sure is odd...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.04,0:26:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the killer is holding the handle, there should be no blood there...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.04,0:26:23.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.31,0:26:26.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there were masks among the masks that were scattered on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.81,0:26:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with blood splattered on them too.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.98,0:26:33.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was found on the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.59,0:26:36.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems to have been splattered with blood at close range.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.92,0:26:41.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think that the killer was wearing this mask when committing the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.26,0:26:45.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so, there may be some traces of the killer left...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.40,0:26:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are there other masks that have been splattered with blood?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.20,0:26:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but it's quite strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.07,0:26:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the other masks had blood only around the mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.08,0:27:00.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Actually, there's a frightening story about the masks of Jofre,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.71,0:27:04.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,saying they suck the very life out of their owners.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.68,0:27:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.22,0:27:09.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could the killer have scattered the masks
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.92,0:27:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,to confuse investigations with occult stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.03,0:27:15.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.33,0:27:19.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I wonder if that's the only reason why the killer scattered the masks?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.43,0:27:23.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, I'm sure there's some other reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.50,0:27:24.97,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If I could only figure that out...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.97,0:27:26.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.08,0:27:28.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Kobayashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, how was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.11,0:27:31.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We checked everywhere around the mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.61,0:27:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but perhaps because of the snow that has accumulated,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.01,0:27:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,there is no sign of the killer having gone in or out!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.12,0:27:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the killer is...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.25,0:27:40.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone inside the mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.65,0:27:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aside from Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and his family, those who were in this mansion are
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.06,0:27:47.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,photographer Masanori Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.59,0:27:51.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,pro baseball player Mamoru Matsudaira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.13,0:27:54.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,popular fortune-teller Haruka Nagara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.47,0:27:58.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,rock singer Toya Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.14,0:28:01.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the victim's secretary, Kazuyo Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.99,0:28:05.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the twin maids, Minaho and Honami Shimogasa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.48,0:28:07.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That makes seven people.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.38,0:28:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can narrow down the suspects a bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.58,0:28:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.75,0:28:26.12,Signs,,0,0,0,,2ND FLOOR
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.75,0:28:26.14,Signs,,0,0,0,,W
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.77,0:28:26.14,Signs,,0,0,0,,E
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.77,0:28:26.14,Signs,,0,0,0,,MASK ROOM
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.32,0:28:16.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't get to Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bedroom on the third floor
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.62,0:28:18.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,without using the stairs in the west wing.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.99,0:28:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the time of the incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.49,0:28:24.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the doors leading to the east and west wings were both locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.16,0:28:26.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This has already been verified.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.20,0:28:27.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.27,0:28:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you couldn't pass from the east wing to the west wing at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.90,0:28:32.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the killer is someone
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.60,0:28:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,who was in the west wing of the mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.04,0:28:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who were in what rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.90,0:28:42.92,Signs,,0,0,0,,E
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.90,0:28:42.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,1ST FLOOR
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.90,0:28:42.88,Signs,,0,0,0,,W
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.34,0:28:49.49,Signs,,0,0,0,,2ND FLOOR
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.24,0:28:40.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, on the first floor of the east wing were Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.58,0:28:42.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the west wing were Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Minaho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.32,0:28:45.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the second floor of the east wing were the three of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.68,0:28:49.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the west wing were Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Matsudaira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Haruka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.49,0:28:52.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see... There are five suspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.93,0:28:56.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Matsudaira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Nagara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.70,0:28:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Minaho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.13,0:29:02.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yes, the messenger of the cursed masks
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.60,0:29:04.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}is one of those five!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.76,0:29:12.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everyone,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.00,0:29:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hate to have to do this, knowing how tired you all must be,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.23,0:29:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I'd like to ask you a few questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.50,0:29:21.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The incident occurred in the early morning, at around 2:30.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.06,0:29:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell me, in order, what you were doing at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.91,0:29:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.35,0:29:32.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was fast asleep in my room until Ran came to wake me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.09,0:29:36.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You got the key and headed for the second floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.52,0:29:38.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where do you keep the key?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.79,0:29:41.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the kitchen wall next to this dining room.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.76,0:29:44.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So anybody could take it and use it at will?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.93,0:29:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the key was definitely there at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.60,0:29:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.58,0:29:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.34,0:29:51.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.74,0:29:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are there any spare keys?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.27,0:29:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are old keys, so we can't make spares.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.98,0:29:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we unlocked the door and went into the mask room,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.98,0:30:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,we noticed that the masks of Jofre were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.58,0:30:08.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was when we heard the groan and loud noise from the third floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.46,0:30:13.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, and while we were waking Minaho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on the extension phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.16,0:30:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} came along.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.24,0:30:18.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was sleeping in my room on the first floor too.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.83,0:30:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I realized that they had come to wake Honami,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.44,0:30:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but I didn't think it was a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.04,0:30:27.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it started getting noisy,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.68,0:30:29.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so I went to the second floor to check things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.71,0:30:33.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was awakened by Honami on the extension phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.55,0:30:35.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,took the key and went to the second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.55,0:30:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was also sleeping in my room,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.02,0:30:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but as it started to get noisy outside, I got up
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.89,0:30:45.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and went out into the corridor just as Minaho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had come up the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.43,0:30:47.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Same with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.53,0:30:49.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.76,0:30:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I heard that you did not appear at the time the corpse was found?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.70,0:30:59.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had too much wine to drink last night and was totally passed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.11,0:31:02.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you didn't notice all the racket going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.84,0:31:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.01,0:31:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, have you ever met Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} before?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.65,0:31:11.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I met her for the first time yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.79,0:31:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.65,0:31:19.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} asked me to check on the accident that took your wife's life 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.89,0:31:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.23,0:31:24.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any idea why?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.40,0:31:26.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.60,0:31:32.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Suo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} asked the old man to check on the accident that took Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s wife's life?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.64,0:31:36.08,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why would she want to check on a traffic accident that happened 20 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.08,0:31:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your mother got into a car accident twenty years ago too, didn't she, Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.22,0:31:46.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.22,0:31:47.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.13,0:31:48.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.52,0:31:51.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will you tell us about the accident that took your wife's life?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.46,0:31:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll find out sooner or later even if I didn't tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.70,0:32:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, my wife was the victim of the car accident that Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mother had caused.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.19,0:32:05.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.27,0:32:08.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you know about it, Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.34,0:32:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No... because I was still only six years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.21,0:32:16.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, how is that traffic accident connected to today's murder case?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.35,0:32:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police think that the murderer is among us, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.22,0:32:24.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way! Is that true, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.37,0:32:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no, not really...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.59,0:32:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recall that it had stopped snowing after 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.63,0:32:34.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll bet you couldn't find traces of the killer on the snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.17,0:32:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is she right, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.34,0:32:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.24,0:32:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's true that there are no signs of the killer having entered or left the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.22,0:32:49.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.88,0:32:51.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean the killer is among us?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.82,0:32:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, since the mask room was locked,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.79,0:32:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer has to be one of the five who were in the west wing!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.39,0:33:06.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Haruka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Matsudaira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or Minaho{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.27,0:33:11.87,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Huh? Wait a sec... That was a strange remark.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.87,0:33:14.09,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why did he say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.61,0:33:17.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's difficult to single out the suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.81,0:33:20.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think there is a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.85,0:33:25.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me that you're going to find the killer using your cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.69,0:33:27.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the looks of the scene of the crime,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.39,0:33:30.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the killer probably was splattered by a lot of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.02,0:33:33.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it is possible to avoid blood on the face by wearing the mask,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.56,0:33:37.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it would not be as easy to remove the blood from the hair and body.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.24,0:33:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! The killer is someone who had time to wipe the splattered blood off!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.57,0:33:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What? Are you saying that I'm the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.11,0:33:48.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only person who had time to wipe blood off
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.74,0:33:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is you, because you weren't at the scene where the body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.71,0:33:54.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.55,0:33:56.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would I have to kill Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.38,0:33:59.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.02,0:34:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cut out your nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.79,0:34:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.96,0:34:04.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You fraud fortune-teller!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.84,0:34:24.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's it! That's what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.48,0:34:30.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I was completely deceived by the trap that the killer had set!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.18,0:34:33.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But now, this farce is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.95,0:34:37.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I've figured out the curse of the masks!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.90,0:34:44.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What's up, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.67,0:34:48.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle Mouri says he has a favor to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.17,0:34:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.81,0:34:56.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the chest over there. Take a look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.38,0:34:59.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh well...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.62,0:35:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.36,0:35:16.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Leave the rest to me, old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.31,0:35:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is the bedroom next door...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.24,0:35:34.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bedroom that looks just like Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s was right next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.05,0:35:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Correct. This room, with the same layout as the crime scene,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.55,0:35:40.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is what helped solve the mystery of the locked doors
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.29,0:35:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,as well as reveal the identity of the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.41,0:35:46.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean Inaba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is not the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.69,0:35:48.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been saying that I'm not!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.83,0:35:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you solved the mystery of the locked doors?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.63,0:35:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I've figured everything out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.63,0:35:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So who is the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.07,0:35:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The killer who killed Beniko Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} in a locked room,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.61,0:36:01.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the Messenger of the Cursed Masks is...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.91,0:36:06.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...you!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.21,0:36:13.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Messenger of the Cursed Masks is...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.62,0:36:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...you!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.15,0:36:16.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toya Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.82,0:36:20.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.89,0:36:21.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unbelievable...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.06,0:36:24.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What on earth are you talking about, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.29,0:36:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could I, who was in the east wing of the mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.40,0:36:29.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,have gone to {\i1}Sensei{\i0}'s bedroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.83,0:36:34.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's true that you could not go to Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.77,0:36:36.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to prove that,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.79,0:36:41.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,you called us on the extension phone just before you committed the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.51,0:36:46.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if he couldn't go to her bedroom, how could he have committed the crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.02,0:36:50.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been suspicious from the time the body was found.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.12,0:36:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I kept wondering why the killer, despite committing the crime behind a locked door,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.49,0:36:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,didn't make her death look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.56,0:37:01.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because he couldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.83,0:37:08.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} without entering her bedroom at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.17,0:37:10.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.07,0:37:12.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without going into her bedroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.94,0:37:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.51,0:37:19.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible, with the help of the cursed masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.08,0:37:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Don't tell me that you really believe in things such as curses?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.59,0:37:32.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. But the masks of Jofre are indeed the key to committing this locked-room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.00,0:37:35.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will replay that method here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.13,0:37:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.04,0:37:37.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.84,0:37:46.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I borrowed a knife that is similar to the murder weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.18,0:37:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a rubber rope attached through the hole at the rear end of the handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.51,0:37:51.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next, the mask.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.83,0:37:56.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rubber rope is passed through both eyes of all the masks,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.29,0:38:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the rubber rope attached to the knife is passed through the mouth hole of all the masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.66,0:38:05.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all of us went to bed, Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.46,0:38:08.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,went to the kitchen to get the key to enter the mask room.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.59,0:38:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stole the masks of Jofre and a knife,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.13,0:38:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then locked the door and returned the key to the kitchen.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.27,0:38:18.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He brought the masks and knife into this room,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.17,0:38:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and carried on with the rubber rope trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.88,0:38:23.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He dropped the masks and the knife
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.41,0:38:25.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,into Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s bedroom through the space between the railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.21,0:38:26.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The size of the space is 5×5 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.85,0:38:29.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A thin mask would easily slide through.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.75,0:38:33.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you really solve the mystery of the locked door doing something like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.94,0:38:36.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, please watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.51,0:38:54.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the last mask!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.65,0:38:59.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After placing all the masks inside the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.82,0:39:02.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he pulled the rubber rope towards himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.80,0:39:26.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, everyone, since one mask is 15 millimeters thick,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.07,0:39:28.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,if 200 are piled up one on top of another,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.31,0:39:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the pile would be 3 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.21,0:39:32.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The position of the neck of the victim asleep in bed
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.78,0:39:35.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was about 3.5 meters from the railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.45,0:39:37.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then what?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.70,0:39:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.48,0:40:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the edge of the knife to the victim's throat is only 10 centimeters.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.15,0:40:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All he had left to do now was to push the masks out using a ruler or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.02,0:40:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By using the stairs that only the people in the east wing of the mansion can climb,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.00,0:40:25.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} killed Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} without setting foot into her room at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.10,0:40:29.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! One of the masks was badly covered blood
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.87,0:40:32.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because it was the mask on the very top, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.77,0:40:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why several masks had blood by the mouth,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.88,0:40:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was because Suo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s splattered on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.48,0:40:41.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally, he severs the rubber rope that was passed through the eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.52,0:40:43.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,of the masks and the handle of the knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.22,0:40:50.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.20,0:40:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's your locked-room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.67,0:41:00.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all rubbish! Just where do you have the proof that I used that trick?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.14,0:41:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you're acting in bad faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.27,0:41:10.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haven't you realized that you've already confessed that you are the killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.88,0:41:12.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.18,0:41:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were being questioned a while ago, you said,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.99,0:41:22.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I noticed that the kids came to wake Honami up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.19,0:41:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, because I was in my room on the first floor then!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.33,0:41:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you said, those kids, who besides Ran were you referring to?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.70,0:41:31.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who else but the kid named Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.73,0:41:34.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh, how strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.30,0:41:37.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't say a word back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.41,0:41:39.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you know I was with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.51,0:41:41.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.84,0:41:45.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, I opened the door a bit and looked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.18,0:41:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I know that you were with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.28,0:41:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.55,0:41:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.25,0:41:54.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it's even stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.62,0:41:57.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I didn't go with Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.79,0:42:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to check if the doors around the house were locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.23,0:42:02.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.33,0:42:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.77,0:42:05.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.83,0:42:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.21,0:42:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did tell Ran and Conan to go get Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.24,0:42:21.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought the two of them went to Honami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s room together,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.18,0:42:24.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,because when you heard me say that, you were on the third floor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.39,0:42:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just because of something like that, you figured...!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.66,0:42:32.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toya! After all {\i1}Sensei{\i0} did for you, how could you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.09,0:42:35.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up! After all she did for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.03,0:42:36.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've got to be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.57,0:42:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That lady blamed the hit-and-run accident that she caused on my mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.30,0:42:42.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and made it look as if she committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.70,0:42:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.51,0:42:48.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true! But I only found out about it two months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.21,0:42:51.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was cleaning out my mother's belongings,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.38,0:42:54.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,when a letter fell out from behind the cover of her diary
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.08,0:42:56.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the truth about the incident was written in it!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.80,0:42:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie! It's all rubbish!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.12,0:43:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's not! Mother had an alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.89,0:43:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The accident occurred on the night of October 31!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.53,0:43:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,October 31...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.03,0:43:12.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s birthday...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.20,0:43:16.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right! Mother was with me all day!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.31,0:43:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means that the one who hit my wife and ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.48,0:43:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...was Suo?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.08,0:43:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, she didn't even know that your wife
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.65,0:43:28.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,was the victim of a traffic accident, Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.58,0:43:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess she asked me to investigate on the case
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.39,0:43:35.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,after she heard Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} talk about it at dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.13,0:43:39.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sensei{\i0} is a fine person who has been hosting charity shows for 15 years!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.83,0:43:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.30,0:43:45.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That lady embezzled the money that was raised to fatten her own pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.50,0:43:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie! {\i1}Sensei{\i0} would never do any such thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.10,0:43:50.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You also got part of the cash, didn't you!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.04,0:43:52.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't talk as if you know nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.88,0:43:59.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted to keep Katagiri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from participating in this corrupt charity
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.21,0:44:01.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,no matter what...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.55,0:44:03.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That lady...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.05,0:44:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beniko Suo was a devil wearing the mask of someone practicing good will!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.62,0:44:11.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think that I felt grateful for her having saved me, all these years...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.06,0:44:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I... I...!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.32,0:45:49.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be that Aikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was possessed by the curse of the masks.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.06,0:45:52.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Curses are only superstitions!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.48,0:46:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A curse! This is a curse!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.58,0:46:15.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's no curse, old man. You're just a klutz.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.64,0:46:29.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That sounded like...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.95,0:46:31.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A gunshot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.85,0:46:40.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.96,0:46:46.89,Signs,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.89,0:46:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint: Rain shower
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.89,0:46:53.46,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The next episode airs April 10!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.46,0:46:55.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next week is the movie, The Last Wizard of the Century!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.69,0:46:56.89,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
